online
{ Louise Kelly, Sarah McCabe and Adrian Weckler 
    December 03 2014 01:28 PM
 https://www.independent.ie/business/irish/check-out-our-top-30-under-30-these-are-the-people-that-you-want-to-be-friends-with-30795572.html }
Yesterday marked a successful day for Stripe when it secured a fresh funding round of €57m, valuing the online payments firm at €2.8bn. Launched by Limerick brothers John (24) and Patrick Collison (26) in 2010, the tech company has steadily risen in wealth and global recognition despite - or perhaps because of - their youth. In this vein, we've taken a look at their counterparts - those of similar age that look set to shape the face of business as we know it. From fashion to funds, politics to property and a mountain of applications for use in the cyber sphere, these are the leaders of our future. * Keyun Ruan (28) Cyber security Originally from Shanghai, Dublin-based and UCD-educated Ruan is one of the world's foremost experts on cybersecurity. She was recently appointed as senior research scientist at the R&D division of Dublin-based online security company Espion and is co-founder of New York cloud forensics training and consultancy organisation Xensix. * Simon Harris (27) Politics 





 
